	Table of Contents
</A>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<BR>
	UNIQURE&nbsp;N.V.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	Notes to the Consolidated Financial Statements (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	For the Years Ended December&nbsp;31, 2013, 2014 and 2015
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	12. Shareholders' (Deficit)/Equity (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On
	July&nbsp;24, 2013 pursuant to agreements with Chiesi Pharmaceutic,&nbsp;S.p.A. the Company raised a total amount of &euro;14&nbsp;million through the issuance of
	1,109,214 class&nbsp;C ordinary shares at a price of &euro;12.60&nbsp;per share.
</FONT>
</P>
<UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	Share Premium
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
</UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Total additions to share premium for the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2015 were &euro;138,692,000 net of costs.
	This increase in share premium was due to the issue of shares as described above.
</FONT>
</P>
<UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	Other Reserves
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
</UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The costs of equity-settled share-based payments to employees are recognized in the Statement of Comprehensive Loss, together with a
	corresponding increase in equity during the vesting period, taking into account (deferral of) corporate income taxes.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;During
	the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, the Company recognized a share-based payment expense of &euro;7,627,000 (2014: &euro;9,464,000), as
	described in Note&nbsp;23. Share-based payment expenses in 2014 include expenses resulting from the accelerated vesting of
	options upon closing of the IPO, as well as the expenses incurred in relation to the granting of options to the management of 4D Molecular Therapeutics.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Share
	based payment expenses for 2015 include amounts associated with the granting of 179,068 Restricted Stock Units in August 2014 and the granting of a total of 1,566,500 options (net
	of forfeitures).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;During
	the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, the Company recognized &euro;1,250,000 as translation adjustments concerning uniQure&nbsp;Inc.; these adjustments
	are included in the Statement of Comprehensive Loss as other comprehensive income.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;As
	at December&nbsp;31, 2015, the Company has legally restricted reserves for the capitalization of Development Costs of &euro;374,000 (2014: &euro;6,811,000) and
	for a currency translation adjustment of &euro;2,411,000 (2014: &euro;1,161,000). Under Dutch law the legally restricted reserve for the capitalization of development Costs is
	non-distributable to the Company's shareholders. Only the reserve for the currency translation adjustment is reflected in the Company's equity, under other comprehensive income.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;No
	tax amounts are included under other comprehensive income, as the Company does not record any income tax expense.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	13. Share Based Payments
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	2012 Share Option Plan
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
</UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At the general meeting of shareholders on February&nbsp;15, 2012, uniQure shareholders approved the adoption of the 2012 Plan. Under
	the 2012 Plan, share options were granted on the date of grant and vest over a period of three years on the basis set out in Note&nbsp;2.22 above. Any options that vest must be exercised by the
	tenth anniversary of the effective date of grant. All options granted under the 2012
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-50
</FONT>
</P>

<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	For the Years Ended December&nbsp;31, 2013, 2014 and 2015
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	13. Share Based Payments (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Plan
	vested in full on the Company's February 2014 IPO. The Company granted 1,907,815 options under this plan.
</FONT>
</P>
<UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	2014 Share Option Plan
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
</UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At the general meeting of shareholders on January&nbsp;9, 2014, uniQure shareholders approved the adoption of the 2014 Incentive
	Plan. At the general meeting of shareholders on June&nbsp;10, 2015 uniQure shareholders approved an amendment of the 2014 Incentice Plan, increasing the shares reserved for issuance by 1,070,000 to
	2,601,471 to allow providing equity-based compensation beyond new hire grants.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Under
	the 2014 Incentive Plan, share options were granted on the date of grant and vest over a period of four years on the basis set out in Note&nbsp;2.22 above. Any options that vest
	must be exercised by the tenth anniversary of the effective date of grant.
</FONT>
</P>
<UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	4D Option Plan
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
</UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Following the agreement between the Company and 4D Molecular Therapeutics, the Company has granted options to purchase an aggregate of
	609,744 ordinary shares in connection with this collaboration, and will recognize resulting share-based payment expense over three years (4D Option Plan).
</FONT>
</P>
<UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	Restricted Stock Units (RSU)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
</UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In 2014 the Company granted 179,068 RSU's for which the Company recognized a share based expense of &euro;1,117,000. Inputs
	to the valuation of the granted RSU's are the share price at date of grant and the anticipated date of full and final vesting. The fair value at grant of the RSU's is determined at $1.8&nbsp;million
	(&euro;1.5&nbsp;million).
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-51
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Of
	the 3,678,606 options outstanding (2014: 3,053,840, 2013: 1,691,844), 1,391,426 options (2014: 1,423,175, 2013: 773,442) were vested and exercisable (within limitations of the
	Company's Insider Trading Policy). The weighted average life of options outstanding as at December&nbsp;31, 2015 is 6.38&nbsp;years. The weighted average exercise price of options vested and
	exercisable as at December&nbsp;31, 2015, is &euro;3.83 for the 2012 plan and $9.76 for the 2014 plan.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	options outstanding at December&nbsp;31, 2015 include 900,000 options (800,000 options granted to the chief executive officer on appointment and 100,000 options granted as an
	incentive to the chief financial officer in August 2015) which are subject to the approval of the Company's shareholders at the 2016 shareholder meeting. The other plans include options granted to the
	shareholders of 4D and 200,000 options granted as an inducement grant in July 2015 to a member of Senior Management (as approved by the 2014 Option plan).
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-52
</FONT>
</P>

</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>

<FONT SIZE=2>
	Closing
	share price on the grant dates.

</FONT>
</DD>

<FONT SIZE=2>
	(2)

	uniQure
	used an estimated volatility figure, which was determined based on volatility analysis of companies in the same sector and of a similar size.

</FONT>
</DD>

	(3)

<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">

	In
	2013 - March 2015: period from grant until the expected exercise date, thereafter the contractual term of 10&nbsp;years.
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	(4)
</FONT>
</DT>

	Company
	currently does not pay dividends and has no plans to do so.

</FONT>
</DD>

	(5)
</FONT>

<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">

	Based
	on Government bonds with a term that is commensurate with the expected term of each option tranche. Also considered is the risk-free rate over the
	performance period for each option tranche.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In
	2013, 301,468 options were granted (of which 252,652 options were granted to members of the Management Board and 10,000 options were granted to a member of the Supervisory Board). A
	total of 210,853 options were forfeited in 2013 (of which 140,652 options were forfeited from a member of the Management Board and 37,507 options were forfeited from a member of the Supervisory
	Board). In November 2013, a total of 5,118 options were exercised.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Under
	the 2014 Option Plan a total of 1,366,500 options were granted in 2015 (of which 1,100,000 options were granted to members of the Management Board and Senior Management) and
	1,115,000 options were granted in 2014 (of which 332,500 options were granted to members of the Management Board and Senior Management). 16,668 of the options granted to the Management Board and
	Senior Management lapsed or were forfeited during 2015 (2014: 0). In 2015 no options (2014: 35,000 options) were granted to members of the Supervisory Board of which in 2015 none lapsed or was
	forfeited (2014: 5,000). Of the remaining 266,500 options granted in 2015 (2014: 747,500 options), 77,424 lapsed or were forfeited in 2015 (2014: 41,250). As of December&nbsp;31, 2015 there were
	3,678,606 options
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-54
</FONT>
</P>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
</P>
<!-- ZEQ.=7,SEQ=180,EFW="2228066",CP="UNIQURE N.V.",DN="1",CHK=602528,FOLIO='F-54',FILE='DISK131:[16ZAV1.16ZAV71201]FW71201A.;19',USER='LFORD',CD=';4-APR-2016;08:36' -->
<A NAME="A2228066Z20-F_HTM_PAGE_FW71201_1_55">
</A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A HREF="#A2228066Z20-F_HTM_BG71201A_MAIN_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<BR>
	UNIQURE&nbsp;N.V.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	Notes to the Consolidated Financial Statements (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	For the Years Ended December&nbsp;31, 2013, 2014 and 2015
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	13. Share Based Payments (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	outstanding.
	An additional &euro;21.6&nbsp;million of share-based expense is expected to be recognized from 2016 through to 2019.
</FONT>
</P>
<UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	Expected option term
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
</UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;uniQure has considered various approaches to take into account the effects of expected early exercise whereby the length of the vesting
	period, the expected share price development, the expected share price volatility and the participants' employee level within the organization have been analyzed. Prior to February 2015 uniQure
	management determined to take the effects of expected early exercise into account by using an estimate of an option's expected life as an input into the Black-Scholes option-pricing model. As
	historical data about employees' exercise behavior was limited, management's estimate is based on a weighted average expected option life for the entire participant group. The resulting expected
	weighted-average life of the options granted is the midpoint between the vesting date and the contractual term of the options. Starting February 2015 the Company is using a Hull&nbsp;&amp; White option
	model. The model captures early exercises by assuming that the likelihood of exercises will increase when the stock-price reaches defined multiples of the strike price. This analysis is included for
	the full contractual term.
</FONT>
</P>
<UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	Valuation of ordinary shares
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
</UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company's shares are listed on NASDAQ (ticker: QURE). At the date of each grant of options subsequent to the transaction between
	uniQure and AMT, and prior to date of listing, the fair value of the ordinary shares is determined by the Management Board and Supervisory Board, and takes into account the most recently available
	valuation of ordinary shares and the assessment of additional objective and subjective factors the Company believes are relevant.
</FONT>
</P>
<UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	Expected volatility
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
</UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;For option grants post April 2012, the volatility has been estimated solely by reference to the historical volatility of the publicly
	traded peer companies. This has resulted in an applied volatility of the options granted in the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2013 and 2014. Based on the limited trading history of the Company's
	shares on NASDAQ, between February&nbsp;5, 2014 and December&nbsp;31, 2015 the volatility for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2015 has been determined at 75%.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Further
	details regarding the total expense recognized in the Statement of Comprehensive Loss for share options granted to members of the Management Board, members of the Supervisory
	Board and Senior Management are set out in Note&nbsp;30. The corresponding increase in equity is separately accounted for as other reserves.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-55
</FONT>
</P>
<HR NOSHADE>

</DIV>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	Hercules borrowings, borrowings derivative
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On June&nbsp;14, 2013 the Company entered into a venture debt loan facility with the Hercules Technology Growth Corp. ("original
	facility"). This $10,000,000 facility agreement was amended and restated on June&nbsp;26, 2014 ("amended facility"). The initial facility provided for an interest-only period of 15&nbsp;months
	following the completion of the Chiesi cooperation (see note&nbsp;7). The amended facility increased the principal amount to $20,000,000, presented net of expenses for facility charges of 1.00% plus
	expenses related to legal counsel. The additional amount of $10,000,000 (&euro;7,344,000) was received net of expenses of $218,000 (&euro;160,000). The net cash inflow was
	$9,782,000 (&euro;7,184,000). As the terms of the amended loan agreement changed significantly compared to the original loan agreement (maturity date, interest rate, payback schedule), the
	Company fully amortized the unamortized transaction costs at issue, resulting in an extra amortization charge through profit and loss in 2014 of $193,000 (&euro;141,000).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	total loan commitment of the amended facility is $20,000,000 with an interest rate of 10.25%, which matures over a period of 48&nbsp;months. Also included are two back-end fees of
	$345,000 and $250,000, due October 2016 and June 2018 respectively. The interest-only period is 18&nbsp;months. The Company was initially required to repay the loan in monthly principal installments
	from January 2016 through June 2018. In December 2015 the interest only period was extended to April 2016 causing an increase in the final installment due in 2018.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;During
	2015, an amount of $2.3&nbsp;million (&euro;2.1&nbsp;million), compared with $2.0&nbsp;million (&euro;1.6&nbsp;million) for 2014, was recorded as
	finance expense in relation to the original and the amended facility.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	total value for the amended loan per December&nbsp;31, 2015 was $20.0&nbsp;million, i.e.&nbsp;&euro;18.6&nbsp;million, (2014: $20.0&nbsp;million,
	i.e.&nbsp;&euro;16.4&nbsp;million) and is recorded net of expenses. The foreign exchange expense on the borrowings was &euro;1.9&nbsp;million in 2015 (2014:
	&euro;1.8&nbsp;million). The fair value of the
	borrowings equals their carrying amount, as the impact of discounting is insignificant as the loan is already amortized at a market conforming interest rate.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-56
</FONT>
</P>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
</P>
<!-- ZEQ.=1,SEQ=182,EFW="2228066",CP="UNIQURE N.V.",DN="1",CHK=795509,FOLIO='F-56',FILE='DISK131:[16ZAV1.16ZAV71201]FY71201A.;10',USER='LFORD',CD=';4-APR-2016;08:44' -->
<A NAME="A2228066Z20-F_HTM_PAGE_FY71201_1_57">
</A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A HREF="#A2228066Z20-F_HTM_BG71201A_MAIN_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<BR>
	UNIQURE&nbsp;N.V.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	Notes to the Consolidated Financial Statements (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	For the Years Ended December&nbsp;31, 2013, 2014 and 2015
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	14. Borrowings (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	original facility included a warrant. The warrant was not closely related to the host contract and was accounted for separately as a financial derivative measured at fair value
	though profit or loss. The fair value of this derivative is &euro;238,000 (2014: 207,000) and is presented within current liabilities. The warrants included in the original loan agreement
	remain in place.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	amended Loan and Security Agreement contains covenants that restrict our ability to, among other things, incur future indebtedness and obtain additional financing, to make
	investments in securities or in other companies, to transfer our assets, to perform certain corporate changes, to make loans to employees, officers and directors, and to make dividend payments and
	other distributions. Further, the Company has periodic reporting requirements and the Company is required to keep a minimum cash balance deposited in bank accounts in the United States, equivalent to
	the lesser of the outstanding balance of principal due and 50% of worldwide cash reserves. This restriction on cash reserves only relates to the location of the cash reserves, but all cash reserves
	are at free disposal of the Company.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	amended Loan and Security Agreement contains default provisions that include the occurrence of a material adverse effect, as defined therein, which would entitle Hercules to declare
	all principal, interest and other amounts owed by us immediately due and payable. As of December&nbsp;31, 2015 the Company was in compliance.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	(Non-current) derivative financial instruments, related party
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;As part of the collaboration agreement (see note&nbsp;4.1) BMS was granted two warrants, the Seventh Collaboration Warrant and the
	Tenth Collaboration Warrant. These warrants provide BMS the right to purchase an additional 10% equity ownership immediately after the exercise of said warrants. The Company has determined that BMS'
	rights to acquire equity in the future are financial instruments, the fair market value of which will reduce the amount of deferred revenue to be recognized on the Company's Consolidated Statement of
	Financial Position.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	(Current) derivative financial instruments, related party
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In 2012 uniQure entered into a convertible loan agreement with four of its major shareholders (Forbion, Gilde, Grupo Netco and Lupus
	Alpha), in respect of unsecured and unsubordinated convertible for a total amount of &euro;3,497,000. In March 2013, uniQure increased the loan by an additional &euro;10,000,000
	investment by Coller Capital. Following the subscription for new equity by Chiesi, on July&nbsp;21, 2013 the full convertible loan of &euro;13,497,000 was converted on July&nbsp;26,
	2013 into new Class&nbsp;A Ordinary Shares, at a conversion price of &euro;10.10 per share. As part of the original convertible loan arrangements the Company also issued warrants to the
	holders of the convertible loan. The warrants associated with the convertible loan, which survived the conversion of the loan, are presented in the Consolidated Statement of Financial Position as at
	December&nbsp;31, 2015 within current liabilities as derivative financial instrument with a fair value of &euro;992,000 (December&nbsp;31, 2014: &euro;645,000). During the
	twelve month period ended December&nbsp;31, 2015 uniQure recognized &euro;&nbsp;347,000 in finance expenses (2014: finance income of &euro;&nbsp;77,000) related
	to fair value changes of the warrants.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-57
</FONT>
</P>
<HR NOSHADE>

<B>
	For the Years Ended December&nbsp;31, 2013, 2014 and 2015
</B>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	15. Financial lease liabilities
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;uniQure leases certain leasehold improvements by means of finance leases including the following:
</FONT>
</P>
<UL>
<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&#149;
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Agreement between Beheersmaatschappij Dienstverlening en Deelneming AZUA&nbsp;BV ("BDDA"), a wholly-owned subsidiary of the AMC, and
	uniQure, regarding leasehold improvements at Meibergdreef, Amsterdam, end at September&nbsp;30, 2016. The rent of the leasehold improvements amounts to &euro;156,000 per year.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
</UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Finance
	lease liabilities are effectively secured as the rights to the leased asset revert to the lessor in the event of default. The carrying amount corresponds to the fair value as
	terms of the contracts were agreed at arm's length and market conditions for such contracts have not subsequently changed. The interest rate imposed by the lessor is 5.5% per annum.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">

	Other current liabilities
</B>
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;As of December&nbsp;31, 2015 and December&nbsp;31, 2014, other current liabilities consisted principally of accruals for services
	provided by vendors but not yet billed, reimbursements received from research and development partners for expenses that have yet to be incurred and miscellaneous liabilities.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;All
	revenues have been earned by Dutch entities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
<U>
	License revenues
</U>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;During
	the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, an amount of &euro;2,854,000 (2014: &euro;883,000 and 2013:
	&euro;440,000) was recognized as license revenues. These amounts relate to the amortization of upfront and target payments received from the Company's collaboration partners and are
	recognized as license revenue over the period of performance.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Upon
	closing of the Commercialization Agreement and the Co-Development and Commercialization Agreement with Chiesi on June&nbsp;30, 2013, the Company received
	&euro;17.0&nbsp;million as a non-refundable upfront payment. Based on an assessment performed by the Company, the &euro;17.0&nbsp;million is amortized on a straight-line
	basis, and presented as license revenues, over a period from July 2013 through September 2032: the date of expiration of the last intellectual property protection related to the Company's
	manufacturing process. The Company determined that the &euro;17.0&nbsp;million of up-front payments received from Chiesi constituted a single unit of accounting.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In
	conjunction with the closing and effective date of the BMS collaboration agreement on May&nbsp;21, 2015, the Company received an upfront, non-refundable cash payment of
	&euro;45.0&nbsp;million ($50.0&nbsp;million). As of the effective date, the Company recorded deferred revenue of &euro;53.2&nbsp;million, which was equal to the upfront
	consideration of &euro;45.0&nbsp;million, plus the premium paid for the initial equity investment over the fair market value of the ordinary shares issued to BMS (valued at
	&euro;10.8&nbsp;million), less the fair market value of the financial instruments linked to the Second Closing and the Seventh and Tenth Collaboration Warrants
	(&euro;2.6&nbsp;million). The deferred revenue will be amortized over a performance period beginning as of the effective date of the collaboration agreement and ending on the nineteenth
	anniversary of the effective date. On July&nbsp;31, 2015 BMS selected the 2nd, 3rd&nbsp;and 4th&nbsp;collaboration targets, triggering a $15.0&nbsp;million target designation payment
	(&euro;13.7&nbsp;million) to the Company. The target designation payment was recorded as deferred revenue on the Company's Statement of Financial Position and will be amortized on a
	straight-line basis over 19&nbsp;years starting August&nbsp;1, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-59
</FONT>
</P>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
</P>
<!-- ZEQ.=4,SEQ=185,EFW="2228066",CP="UNIQURE N.V.",DN="1",CHK=59298,FOLIO='F-59',FILE='DISK131:[16ZAV1.16ZAV71201]FY71201A.;10',USER='LFORD',CD=';4-APR-2016;08:44' -->
<A NAME="A2228066Z20-F_HTM_PAGE_FY71201_1_60">
</A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A HREF="#A2228066Z20-F_HTM_BG71201A_MAIN_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<BR>
	UNIQURE&nbsp;N.V.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	Notes to the Consolidated Financial Statements (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	For the Years Ended December&nbsp;31, 2013, 2014 and 2015
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	17. Revenues and deferred revenues (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
<U>
	Collaboration revenues
</U>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Collaboration
	revenues, which are typically related to cost reimbursement from collaborators for the Company's performance of research and development services
	under the respective agreements, are recognized on the basis of labour hours valued at a contractually agreed rate. Cost reimbursements to which the Company is entitled under agreements are recognized
	as collaboration revenues in the same quarter of the recorded cost they are intended to compensate.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;During
	the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, an amount of &euro;6,271,000 (2014: &euro;3,802,000 and 2013: &euro;2,505,000) was recognized as
	collaboration revenues. These amounts relate to reimbursement of certain approved research and development expenses under the Company's collaboration agreements with Chiesi, BMS and Treeway.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Specifically,
	the Company is eligible for reimbursement from Chiesi for 50% of the approved development costs related to the development of AMT-060 for haemophilia B and for 50% of the
	approved costs related to the Company's Phase&nbsp;IV study and registry for Glybera. Additionally, the Company is eligible for reimbursement from BMS for 100% of the approved research costs related
	to S100A1 and any other agreed targets contemplated in the collaboration agreement. The increase in the current period amount reflects the reimbursement of certain approved research expenses for
	S100A1 under the Company's collaboration agreement with BMS.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
<U>
	Product revenue
</U>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Product
	revenue recognized in 2015 relates to the sale of Glybera.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	18. Expenses by Nature, Cost of goods sold
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In 2015 Cost of goods sold include cost of raw materials, directly attributable labor costs and directly related charges by third party service providers, and the royalties and other
	related payments to third parties the Company must make under the license agreements covering various aspects of the technology underlying the composition and manufacture of Glybera. In addition Cost
	of goods sold in 2015 include amortization of intangible assets of &euro;0.3&nbsp;million as well as amounts related to the repayment of government grants.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In
	2013 Cost of goods sold resulted from a &euro;0.8&nbsp;million a repayment of a technical development loan to the Dutch government. This repayment was triggered by the
	&euro;2.0&nbsp;million upfront payment for the Glybera program that was collected from Chiesi in the second quarter of 2013.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-60
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee
	benefit expenses for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2015 include share-based payments of &euro;7.6&nbsp;million (2014: &euro;9.5&nbsp;million) of
	which &euro;1.2&nbsp;million (2014: &euro;6.3&nbsp;million) is related to the 4D Option Plan. Share-based payments, recorded under employee benefit expenses, for the year
	ended December&nbsp;31, 2013 were &euro;2,023,000.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	19. Research and development expenses
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Research and development expenses increased from &euro;33,932,000 in the period ended December&nbsp;31, 2014 to &euro;46,781,000 in the period ended
	December&nbsp;31, 2015. This increase reflected the expansion of the research and development activities to support the additional development and clinical activities associated with the
	Phase&nbsp;I/II study of AMT-060, the build-up of staff in the Lexington facility, as well as the further development of Glybera and the other product candidates.
</FONT>
</P>

<A NAME="A2228066Z20-F_HTM_PAGE_FY71201_1_62">
</A>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<A HREF="#A2228066Z20-F_HTM_BG71201A_MAIN_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<BR>
	UNIQURE&nbsp;N.V.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	Notes to the Consolidated Financial Statements (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	For the Years Ended December&nbsp;31, 2013, 2014 and 2015
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	19. Research and development expenses (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Research
	and development expenses increased from &euro;13,182,000 in the period ended December&nbsp;31, 2013 to &euro;33,932,000 in the period ended December
	2014, due to the expansion of the Company's research and development activities and planned clinical study of AMT-060, the planned commercial launch of Glybera in the European Union, the build-up of
	staff in the Lexington facility, as well as the further development of Glybera and the other product candidates.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	20. Selling, general and administrative expenses
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selling, general and administrative expenses increased from &euro;11,167,000 for the period ended December&nbsp;31, 2014 to &euro;19,317,000 for the period ended
	December&nbsp;31, 2015. The increase is driven by an increase in professional fees around corporate transactions, the build out of the administrative functions to meet the compliance requirements of
	a public company and the engagement of third party consultants to support the Company in various corporate and administrative activities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selling,
	general and administrative expenses decreased from &euro;11,628,000 for the period ended December&nbsp;31, 2013 to &euro;11,167,000 for the period ended
	December&nbsp;31, 2014. The decrease resulted principally from the high legal and audit related expenses incurred in 2013 for the preparation of the Company's initial public offering, partially
	offset by an increase of expenses in the period ended December&nbsp;31, 2014, related to being a public company, and the continued build-out of the administrative functions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	21. Other income / other losses
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;uniQure's other income consists of government subsidies and grants that support uniQure's research efforts in defined research and development projects.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Other
	income was &euro;708,000 in 2015 (2014: &euro;773,000, 2013&nbsp;&euro;585,000) and relates to grants received and rebates on payroll
	taxes. In 2014 uniQure,&nbsp;Inc., the Company's wholly owned subsidiary, received a grant from Massachusetts Life Science Company under its Job Incentive Program (New Job Creation). The monthly
	amortization (&euro;13,000) of this grant started in December 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	other gains / losses line represents the currency effect from regular operations whereas the currency risk associated with borrowings is presented under Finance Income or Expense.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-62
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Finance
	expenses related to the venture debt facility result from foreign exchanges losses between the USD and Euro of &euro;1,911,000 for the twelve month period ended
	December&nbsp;31, 2015 (2014: &euro;1,834,000) as well as interest expense of &euro;2,096,000 (2014: &euro;1,598,000).
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="RIGHT" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	(431
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
	)
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<!-- END OF USER-SPECIFIED TAGGED TABLE -->
</DIV>
</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;As
	part of the acquisition of InoCard in Germany in 2014 the Company capitalized the fair value of the acquired in progress research and development as an intangible asset. For tax
	purposes, research results are being expensed. The Company recognized a deferred tax liability at 30% of the asset's fair value, i.e.&nbsp;&euro;1,379,000. Following the acquisition the
	research at the German site was effectively integrated into uniQure's Dutch operations. In December 2015 uniQure legally transferred, with economic effect as of the acquisition date, the intellectual
	property of the German entity to a Dutch entity. In respect of the transfer the Company recognized a &euro;0.9&nbsp;million
	deferred tax asset for the excess of the underlying patent's tax basis over the patent's carrying amount. This immaterial error was corrected through a reduction of goodwill recorded in the
	acquisition as at December&nbsp;31, 2015 (see note&nbsp;2.2.a). The patent formed an integral part of the acquired research and development intangible asset. Consequently the intangible was
	transferred along with the patent resulting in remeasuring the associated deferred tax liability of &euro;479,000 at the Dutch purchaser's effective tax rate of 25%. The Dutch entity as
	from the economic transfer date onward funds the research of the German site, which allowed the German entity to utilize the 2014 losses carried forward resulting in current tax expenses for 2014 and
	2015 of &euro;47,622.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	expenses not deductible for tax purposes are largely driven by the Company's share-based compensation plans for an amount of &euro;1,907,000 in 2015 (2014:
	&euro;2,365,000).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	net result in 2013 for uniQure&nbsp;Inc. (USA) translated into taxable loss of nil as for tax purposes under Sec 195 (startup costs) all book expenses were capitalized to offset
	the loss. At the time
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-64
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>

	UNIQURE&nbsp;N.V.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	Notes to the Consolidated Financial Statements (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	For the Years Ended December&nbsp;31, 2013, 2014 and 2015
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	23. Income tax expense (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	of
	filing its 2014 tax return in September 2015 the Company revised its assumption that it had started an "active trade or business" in 2014 and consequently capitalized a further $3.6&nbsp;million
	of start-up expenses. uniQure&nbsp;Inc. intends to capitalized $18.9&nbsp;million in start-up losses for 2015. Future amortization of start-up cost will be available for offset against future
	taxable income. uniQure&nbsp;Inc. will additionally benefit from a reversal of accruals at the time these will be settled in cash. These temporary differences will roll up into future operating
	losses. uniQure&nbsp;Inc. currently does not expect to utilize the above tax benefits within the foreseeable future and therefore did not recognize a deferred tax asset.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Under
	Dutch income tax law a tax loss carry-forward is subject to a time limitation of nine years. Losses incurred in the years up to 2006 can still be offset against profits up to and
	including 2015. In connection with the transfer of the AMT Business from AMT to uniQure, uniQure has discussed with Belastingdienst, the Dutch tax authorities, the transfer of all accumulated tax
	losses that relate to the AMT Business, excluding tax losses relating specifically to the activities of the AMT legal entity.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In
	order to promote innovative technology development activities and investments in new technologies, a corporate income tax incentive has been introduced in Dutch tax law called the
	Innovations Box. For the qualifying profits, the Company effectively owes only 5% income tax (should available tax losses carried forward be utilized) instead of the general tax rate of 25.0%. Because
	uniQure is loss-making it has not currently made any application to the tax authorities for such an agreement, but intends to do so when it reaches profitability.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	Dutch fiscal unity has as of December&nbsp;31, 2015 an estimated &euro;185,476&nbsp;thousand (2014: &euro;145,107&nbsp;thousand) of taxable losses that
	can be offset in the following nine years. The expiration dates of these Dutch losses, is summarized in the following table. In the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, the amount of unused tax losses
	that expired was &euro;4,228&nbsp;thousand (2014: &euro;1,336&nbsp;thousand).
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">

<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Basic loss per share is calculated by dividing the profit attributable to equity holders of the Company by the weighted average number
	of shares outstanding during the period.

</EFX_STOCKHOLDERS_EQUITY>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	Diluted loss per share
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Diluted loss per share is calculated by adjusting the weighted average number of ordinary shares outstanding to assume conversion of
	all dilutive potential ordinary shares. Due to the fact that the Company is loss making, all potential ordinary shares would have an antidilutive effect, if converted, and thus have been excluded from
	the computation of loss per share.
</FONT>
</P>

</B>

<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company did not declare dividends for the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, 2014 and 2013.

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>

	27. Commitments and Contingent liabilities
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	Royalties and milestones
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In the course of its business uniQure enters as a licensee into contracts with other parties with regard to the development and
	marketing of its pipeline products. Among other payment obligations, the Company is obligated to pay royalties to the licensors based on future sales
	levels and milestone payments whenever defined milestones are met. As both future sales levels and the timing and
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT SIZE=2>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	achievement
	of milestones are uncertain, the financial effect of these agreements cannot be estimated reliably.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	Operating lease commitments
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;uniQure leases various office space and laboratory space under operating lease agreements. The Company leases its headquarters under an
	agreement between uniQure and Academisch Medisch Centrum ("AMC"), represented by Beheersmaatschappij Dienstverlening en Deelneming AZUA&nbsp;B.V. ("BDDA") and Amsterdam Vector
	Productions&nbsp;B.V. ("AVP"), both subsidiaries of AMC (Second Rental Agreement) in respect of facilities located at Meibergdreef 61 Amsterdam, from October&nbsp;1, 2005 until September&nbsp;30
	2016, and an agreement for the lease of facilities at Meibergdreef 57, Amsterdam, from July&nbsp;1, 2006 until December&nbsp;31, 2017. The aggregate annual lease payments amount to
	&euro;798,000. On March&nbsp;17, 2015 the Company signed a further agreement with AMC for the lease of office space at Tafelbergweg 51, Amsterdam until December&nbsp;31, 2017.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On
	April&nbsp;14, 2015 the Company entered into a lease agreement with Jan Snel&nbsp;B.V. in respect of laboratory facilities located on AMC grounds, from October&nbsp;12, 2015
	until October&nbsp;11, 2018. The Company started using these facilities on October&nbsp;12, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In
	November 2015 the Company concluded an overall agreement with AMC which entitles the Company to occupy the Amsterdam facilities up to a maximum of December&nbsp;31, 2019. The
	Company expects to leave the facilities at December&nbsp;31, 2016 as a result of the new lease agreement entered in March 2016 (refer to note&nbsp;31).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	lease expenditure charged to the Statement of Comprehensive Loss for Amsterdam-based operating leases amounts to &euro;868,000 in the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2015
	(2014: &euro;550,000, 2013: &euro;542,000). The future aggregate minimum lease payments under non-cancellable operating leases are as follows:
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On
	July&nbsp;24, 2013, uniQure entered into an agreement for the lease of facilities at 113 Hartwell Avenue, Lexington, Massachusetts, United States that became effective from
	November&nbsp;5, 2013 onwards until November&nbsp;5, 2023. uniQure has an option to extend the lease for up to an additional 10&nbsp;years. The aggregate lease payments for the period to
	November&nbsp;5, 2023 amount to $18,937,000
	(&euro;17,278,000), including an initial rent-free period of seven months from the commencement of the lease which was effective at November&nbsp;5, 2013.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	lease payments under an operating lease will be recognized as an expense on a straight line basis over the full duration of the lease, taking into account the lease incentives in a
	total amount of $7,259,000 (&euro;6,469,000) as received from the landlord. This results in a monthly expense of $92,680
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-67
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	Grant commitments
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;From October&nbsp;1, 2000 until May&nbsp;31, 2005, AMT (uniQure's predecessor entity) received a technical development loan from
	the Dutch government in relation to development of Glybera. This grant includes a repayment clause in the event the Company generates revenues from the related project. AMT received total grants of
	&euro;3,605,000 relating to eligible project costs in the grant period. The grant amount received bears interest of 5.7% per annum and must be repaid in the period January&nbsp;1, 2008
	through December&nbsp;31, 2019 as a percentage of revenues
	which are derived from product sales of Glybera. If future royalty payments are not sufficient to repay the grant on or prior to December&nbsp;31, 2019, or if there are no revenues generated, the
	remaining balance will be forgiven. Repayment obligations continue to apply if the product is not commercialized or transferred to others. The total amount of the contingent commitment as at
	December&nbsp;31, 2015 was &euro;6,154,000 (2014: &euro;5,822,000), comprising the original total amount of the grant together with accrued interest.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	28. Related-party transactions
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In the period ended December&nbsp;31, 2015 and 2014, the Management Board and other Senior Management received regular salaries and contributions to post-employment schemes.
	Additionally, selected members of the Supervisory Board received compensation for their services in the form of cash compensation. The Company entered into share-based transaction with the
	shareholders of 4D. One of 4D's managing directors currently serves on our Supervisory Board (see notes&nbsp;2.22 and 13).
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-68
</FONT>

<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	Notes to the Consolidated Financial Statements (Continued)

<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	For the Years Ended December&nbsp;31, 2013, 2014 and 2015
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	28. Related-party transactions (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	Company recognizes shareholders holding more than 5% of the Company's ordinary shares also as related parties. During the period January&nbsp;1, 2014 and December&nbsp;31, 2015
	the following parties beneficially held more than 5% of the Company's ordinary shares.
</FONT>
</P>
<UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Bristol
	Myers Squibb
<BR>
	Chiesi Farmaceutici S.p.A
<BR>
	Coller Capital
<BR>
	Fidelity Management&nbsp;&amp; Research Company
<BR>
	Forbion Capital Partners
<BR>
	Gilde Healthcare Partners
<BR>
	Lupus Alpha PE Champions
</FONT>
</P>
</UL>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Funds
	affiliated with Forbion Capital partners have a material interest in the Company. In addition, Professor Sander van Deventer and Mr.&nbsp;Sander Slootweg, who were appointed as
	members of the Supervisory Board of uniQure on April&nbsp;5, 2012, are each partners of Forbion.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On
	April&nbsp;6, 2015 the Company and Bristol Myers Scquibb ("BMS") entered into various commercial and investment agreements. On August&nbsp;7, 2015 BMS increased its share in the
	Company from 4.9% acquired in June 2015 to 9.9%.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Chiesi
	became a related party following the commercial and investment agreements concluded with the Company on June&nbsp;30, 2013, and Coller Capital became a related party following
	the conversion of the convertible loan in July 2013.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Funds
	affiliated with Lupus Alpha, Fidelity and Gilde Healthcare have or held a material interest in the Company.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	Transactions
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The related parties identified above participated in the following transactions during the periods ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, and
	December&nbsp;31, 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The
	Company had a receivable outstanding with BMS of &euro;927,412 as at December&nbsp;31, 2015. These amounts related to reimbursable expenses incurred in connection with
	the Company's collaboration agreement with BMS. During the twelve month period ended December&nbsp;31, 2015 the Company generated &euro;2,103,963 in collaboration revenues. For a further
	description of BMS related transactions please refer to notes&nbsp;1, 3, 4, 14 and 17.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;During
	the twelve month period ended December&nbsp;31, 2015 the Company generated &euro;4,167,129 (2014: &euro;3,292,000) in revenues with Chiesi. As of
	December&nbsp;31, 2015 the Company has a receivable outstanding with Chiesi of &euro;2,864,943 (2014: &euro;2,404,000).
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-69
</FONT>
</P>

<DL COMPACT>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	(1)
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	The
	share-based payment reflects the value of equity-settled share options expensed during the year, as required by IFRS&nbsp;2.
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	(2)
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Following
	the combination of uniQure and AMT on April&nbsp;5, 2012, Professor van Deventer has received no remuneration until after the IPO.
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	(3)
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Resigned
	December&nbsp;31, 2014.
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	(4)
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Mr.&nbsp;Slootweg
	received no remuneration until after the IPO, resigned on June&nbsp;10, 2015.
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
</DD>

<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The total remuneration (excluding share-based payments) paid to or for the benefit of members of the Management Board and Senior
	Management in 2015 amounted to approximately &euro;4,000,000 (2014: &euro;2,670,000).

	The

	in 2014 to Jorn Aldag.

<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	(3)
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Joern
	Aldag resigned from the Management Board and as Chief executive officer effective December&nbsp;17, 2015.
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
</DD>
<DT STYLE='FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;MARGIN-BOTTOM:-11PT;'>
<FONT SIZE=2>
	(4)
</FONT>
</DT>
<DD STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	Matthew
	Kapusta joined in January 2015. He was appointed to the Management Board at our 2015 annual general meeting in June 2015.
</FONT>
</DD>
</DL>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On
	December&nbsp;17, 2015 the Company and Mr.&nbsp;Aldag agreed to terminate his employment as at August&nbsp;31, 2016. Mr.&nbsp;Aldag will continue to be employed and serve as
	an advisor to the Supervisory Board. At the end of his 8&nbsp;month service period he will be entitled to receive &euro;22,780 in termination benefits. Mr.&nbsp;Aldag was granted a
	bonus of &euro;689,716 in recognition of the transformational BMS Collaboration agreement and his options under the 2014 share incentive plan will accelerate in full as of the termination
	date. On January&nbsp;29, 2016 the parties amended the termination agreement.
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-71
</FONT>
</P>

	Table of Contents
</A>

<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<BR>
	UNIQURE&nbsp;N.V.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	Notes to the Consolidated Financial Statements (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
	For the Years Ended December&nbsp;31, 2013, 2014 and 2015
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	29. Key Management Compensation (Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	repayable
	to uniQure on sale of the related Company's ordinary shares or on the respective employee ceasing to be employed by the Company.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	30. Litigation and Arbitration
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On December&nbsp;11, 2013, the Company received a formal request for arbitration from Extera Partners, a consulting firm based in Cambridge, Massachusetts, alleging a fee to be due in
	respect of consulting services provided to the Company in connection with a partnering transaction. The International Court of Arbitration at the International Chamber of Commerce received the request
	for arbitration on December&nbsp;12, 2013. The amount claimed is $100,000 plus 2.5% of all proceeds, including equity investments, the Company received from Chiesi pursuant to its collaboration
	agreements entered into in the second quarter of 2013. The Company's engagement letter with Extera Partners contains a cap limiting the maximum liability to &euro;5,000,000.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On
	May&nbsp;12, 2014, the ICC appointed and confirmed a sole arbitrator. On October&nbsp;1, 2014, Extera Partners&nbsp;LLC filed its Statement of Case that includes an estimated
	claim based on the formula mentioned above and on Extera's estimate of potential future revenues. An evidentiary hearing took place in July 2015 and post hearing briefs and reply submissions were
	filed in October 2015. The Company has denied the claim and intends to vigorously defend against it.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-0PT;" -->
	31. Events after the reporting date
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;;MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>
<I>
<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"MARGIN-LEFT:10.0PT;TEXT-INDENT:-10.0PT;" -->
	New lease Amsterdam
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On March&nbsp;1, 2016 the Company entered into a 16&nbsp;year lease contract for a new 9,600 square-meter facility in Amsterdam.
	The lease commences on March&nbsp;1, 2016. The Company intends to consolidate its current three Amsterdam sites at the new site in December 2016. The future aggregate minimum lease payments under
	non-cancellable amount to &euro;21.1&nbsp;million.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
	F-74
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES;">
<FONT SIZE=2>
<B>

<A NAME="FIS_EXHIBIT_12"></A>
<BR>
<DIV>
<P ALIGN="RIGHT" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	EXHIBIT&nbsp;12.1
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Certification by the Chief Executive Officer
<BR>
	Pursuant to Section&nbsp;302 of the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	I, Daniel Soland, certify that:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;I have reviewed this annual report on Form&nbsp;20-F of uniQure N.V. (the &#147;Company&#148;);
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Based on my knowledge, this report does not contain any untrue statement of a material fact or omit to state a material fact necessary to make the statements made, in light of the circumstances under which such statements were made, not misleading with respect to the period covered by this report;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Based on my knowledge, the financial statements, and other financial information included in this report, fairly present in all material respects the financial condition, results of operations and cash flows of the Company as of, and for, the periods presented in this report;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company&#146;s other certifying officer and I are responsible for establishing and maintaining disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Exchange Act Rules&nbsp;13a-15(e)&nbsp;and 15d-15(e)) and internal control over financial reporting (as defined in Exchange Act Rules&nbsp;13a 15(f)&nbsp;and 15d 15(f)) for the Company and have:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	a.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Designed such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused such disclosure controls and procedures to be designed under our supervision, to ensure that material information relating to the Company, including its consolidated subsidiaries, is made known to us by others within those entities, particularly during the period in which this report is being prepared;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	b.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Designed such internal control over financial reporting, or caused such internal control over financial reporting to be designed under our supervision, to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	c.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Evaluated the effectiveness of the Company&#146;s disclosure controls and procedures and presented in this report our conclusions about the effectiveness of the disclosure controls and procedures, as of the end of the period covered by this report based on such evaluation;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	d.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Disclosed in this report any change in the Company&#146;s internal control over financial reporting that occurred during the period covered by the annual report that has materially affected, or is reasonably likely to materially affect, the Company&#146;s internal control over financial reporting; and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT .5IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company&#146;s other certifying officer and I have disclosed, based on our most recent evaluation of internal control over financial reporting, to the Company&#146;s auditors and the audit committee of the Company&#146;s board of directors (or persons performing the equivalent functions):
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	a.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;All significant deficiencies and material weaknesses in the design or operation of internal control over financial reporting which are reasonably likely to adversely affect the Company&#146;s ability to record, process, summarize and report financial information; and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 1.0IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	b.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Any fraud, whether or not material, that involves management or other employees who have a significant role in the Company&#146;s internal control over financial reporting.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Date: April&nbsp;4, 2016
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
